This paper is about synthesizing realistic videos of humans using neural networks, which involves computer vision (CV) and graphics (GR) techniques. The proposed method relies on convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which are commonly used in multimedia (MM) and machine learning (LG) research. Additionally, the paper involves the learning of fine-scale details, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (AI) research. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.LG, and cs.AI, in that order.
